getChecksum(address).details: Get a checksummed string hex representation of an account address.

params.account: address The account to get the checksum for.

returns.accountChecksum: The checksummed account string in ASCII format. Note that leading "0x" is not included.

getChecksumCapitalizedCharacters(address.details: Get a fixed-size array of whether or not each character in an account will be capitalized in the checksum.

params.account: address The account to get the checksum capitalization information for.

returns.characterCapitalized: A fixed-size array of booleans that signify if each character or "nibble" of the hex encoding of the address will be capitalized by the checksum.

isChecksumValid(string).details: Determine whether a string hex representation of an account address matches the ERC-55 checksum of that address.

params.accountChecksum: string The checksummed account string in ASCII format. Note that a leading "0x" MUST NOT be included.

returns.ok: A boolean signifying whether or not the checksum is valid.
